Higher Education, Science and InnovationÂ Minister Dr Blade Nzimande is expected to release the results of the second part of a public survey looking at the impact of the novel coronavirus on South Africans. The Human Sciences Research Council (HSRC) announced the launch of the public survey to better understand what the South African public knows about Covid-19, the state of readiness to deal with this global pandemic and how they felt about it on 27 March. The survey came within the context of a rapidly rising infection rate in South Africa, which necessitated a 21-day nationwide lockdown to help control the spread of the virus. The lockdown was further extended until the end of April.The second round of the survey, which was conducted from 7 April to 14 April, looked specifically at the lockdown as implemented from 27 March to 16 April. WATCH LIVE: 